, a level of precision comparable to that afforded by the current Type Ia SNe sample. Asserting a ﬂat spatial geometry, we ﬁnd that, in combination with WMAP, H0 = 69.7−+45..90 km s−1 Mpc−1 and w = −0.94−+00..1179 (68\% CL), suggesting that the observations of B1608+656 constrain w as tightly as the current Baryon Acoustic Oscillation data do.},
